		<title>18SACRISTON PIT P3</title>
		<content>                                       
    The conditions are rough at the    
 coal face :-                          
    the seams are an average of        
 eighteen inches high and are sometimes
 wet and dusty.                        
                                       
    Mining has not changed a great deal
 at Sacriston during the miner's       
 working life :-                       
    his main tools are still the pick  
 shovel and " sticker " ( a big hammer 
 with a point at one end. )            
                                       
    Five pit ponies are still in use.  
                                       
    Dangerous gases are dispersed by   
 increasing the level of underground   
 ventilation  and nearly all the rules 
 of the mine are linked to safety.     
                                       
                                       </content>
